        "timestamp": "2019-12-04 17:50:52.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nI ran a test to check on output based on <property name=..> change, there are some differences in the logging at the places where the lines were split.   I am mostly concerned with the logback.xml under src/main/resources (although not sure why it was placed there in the first place).\n\nThese are some differences (note the additional whitespaces matching the line breaks):\n\n2019-12-04T17:31:06.381Z|||Thread-54|    |||DEBUG||||    |com.att.eelf.debug||POLICY-500I INFO: dbAudit: Exiting\n\nvs\n\n2019-12-04T17:41:04.161Z|||Thread-53||||DEBUG|||||com.att.eelf.debug||POLICY-500I INFO: dbAudit: Exiting\n\nThese could be a problem for log parsing tools on the policy/engine side.",
        "patchset_number": 2
